caption: This has quickly become a brunch favorite. Their bowls are delicious and super filling, and the staff is always friendly.
Very good breakfast.  The Armature Works is enjoyable.

The food was great - Graze Burger, Brussel Sprouts and Sweet Potato Fries. The customer service was awesome ended up sitting at the bar and the staff although busy was friendly and efficient you really know they enjoy their job.
Came for coffee and saw they had breakfast. Best cheese grits I’ve had in town. Bacon egg and cheese bagel was delicious
If u have a meeting this please is great
Awesome customer service! Food was delicious and served hot!
Delicious food
The Graze Burger was amazing 😋 Highly recommend this place. Very clean and excellent service 🤍
Wonderful BLT! Added a couple eggs over to it and it made for a superb breakfast sandwich!
My favorite grits in town! Helen is the absolute best- great breakfast spot!

I gave a 1 star because although the food is good the service is not. I live pretty close by and I’ve tried almost every spot in Armature Works. I’m pretty sure the rude distasteful woman I’ve encountered a few times... is Heather (I could have the name incorrect). The first time her boss had to force her to apologize for her rudeness. Today I bought an amazing breakfast from another restaurant inside of Armature Works called [Kū bå]. Fantastic breakfast! Well I chose to sit by the open window seating by Graze when Heather said to me “you know our breakfast is better” that is very unprofessional! I thought the restaurants were more supportive of each other and more like a family. I think they need new hired help because I don’t believe her attitude will change.
Food is very good. Loved the street tots. The tartine was awesome, too!

Found this place on Instagram and finally got around to trying it! It did not disappoint! The creamy cheese grits were outstanding and the servers were friendly and knowledgeable! Can't wait to visit the stand alone location on Dale Mabry!
LOVE this place and the people! Always friendly. Great breakfast and burgers, but my absolute favorite is the cheesy grits. Best I’ve ever had. Great atmosphere as part of armature works
Food was great. Really enjoyed the breakfast bowl with grits.

Delicious and healthy options for Armature Works. Fits perfectly with specialty diets (keto), and won't break the bank. Fresh ingredients and friendly service. My go-to at AW when I'm not feeling adventurous- their menu is dependable. Ordered the burger and I would have taken a picture but it was too delicious. You won't regret enjoying a meal here.
Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop. The bill won't break you.
The staff was very friendly and attentive.
I had the chicken and waffles tonight. The chicken was really dried out as if it was fried, sat out and they refried to heat it up. The waffle was basic. The maple bacon syrup was ok.
This place is so good, I have yet to get something from here that I didnt love! Very unique menu and good sized portions! The sweet potato fries are a must
Cute little spot with a cool view & close to a lot of other small restaurants/shopping market. Chicken & waffles was so bomb!
Great food
Food looked really good however it was not very flavorful.
I wish there were more places like this around town. The service was very kind and attentive. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
Really good BYO BOWL for breakfast
Everyone at our table was very satisfied. Will surely make a return trip. The bill was decent.

this restaurant is above and beyond expectations! believe it or not my dad is one of the owners of graze and has done a lot for this place! he works so hard to get me and my other siblings what we need and we really appreciate all he has done, plus we get great food!  10/10 recommend!
Food was AMAZING, I got the macaroni and cheese with chicken and sweet potato fries. I live in Kissimmee, FL. I'd literally drive back just for their food again. Lol

As you see from the other reviews, HORRIBLE customer service, which in term makes a bad experience which makes the food come out. It as appetizing! I literally watched this play call the guards to KICK OUT a family with a baby child because the serves were giving them attitude and couldn’t handle a professional response from them! How can you kick out a family from a family place during the day??!! This place needs to be shut down  Update: And this was Graze 1910 that kicked the family out, they told the security guards and the guards even said they have to listen to the restaurant. Clearly from the owners responds. “The fish rots from the head down.” Meaning you are a bad leader hence why your staff acts like this  Also, Stop blaming it on market hall, as your other reviews. Maybe start by removing Amanda . As a leader, blame your self and work on it
Horrible service and okay food
Great options for health-conscious individuals! Breakfast all day, great coffee, and flavorful bowls. Don't forget the views!

Everything I can find online says they open at 8am Mon-Sat, but this does not appear to be up to date. I stood in front for 20 minutes while the people in the back ignored me but no one would acknowledge my presence or tell me what time they actually open.

My husband and I went there to celebrate his first Father’s Day on Sunday and we had a bad experience with Alison. From the very beginning she had an attitude. We ordered our food and sat right in front where she can see us. We patiently waited to receive our text to let us know when the food was done. Alison was too busy flirting with this guy that she ignored the fact that our food sat on the counter ready for 20 minutes. We never received a text so at first we didn’t know that our food was ready. She didn’t even bother to look to see who’s plate was sitting on the counter. As the cook placed people’s orders on the counter, she immediately called their name so they got there food. We watched her the whole time and kept wondering if that was our food sitting in the counter getting cold but we didn’t get the text so we continued to wait. After 20 minutes of the food getting cold, she looks at us and asked us if that was our food sitting on the counter. At this point we are very upset because she never looked to see who’s food that was. We had to wait even longer so the cook can make our food again. Alison never apologized nor did she care that we had to wait. Very poor customer service. She gave excellent customer service to the guy she was flirting with but failed to even acknowledge that there’s a plate sitting on the counter unclaimed.
Terrible service and Amanda was disrespectful
Got to try the Street Tots.
I love this place. Their burgers are pretty good 😊
The food was awesome. Short wait time for the food to come out. Very pleasant and helpful staff. I’ll definitely be back! This is a new favorite.
Great food and friendly staff.
Conceited server. Waste of your time.
I had the BYO Bowl.......the cheese grits are so worth it! We sat at the bar and the staff are great to interact with. Very good attention to detail even at their busy time. Will for sure come back!
Typical “bowl” place and prices reflect it.$$$ Good food in moderate portion size. Friendly service and many other places in the court to choose from.
Food was amazing. Burger was delicious and chicken sandwich was something special. Lots of good drink choices and something for everyone. Highly recommend!
Love love love the chicken and waffles!!!!

This place has officially been placed on my favorites list... I wasn't sure what to expect at first... My wife pointed it out first so of course I followed... I don't know what was more amazing the burger or the sweet potato waffle fries with marshmallow drizzle... I've been fighting the urge to go back so soon... I have eaten at just about every spot in Armature Works and hands down Graze has the best burger and fries combo.

Oh my goodness! This place was so beautiful, I can't hype up the atmosphere enough-- It was very well maintained also! I got a salad at Graze and did not regret it, the salad was made up of greens with chicken and a citrus dressing that was to die for (and they gave plenty of it)! My only qualm was that the price was a bit much, but my experience was one for the books! HIGHLY RECOMMEND 10/10
Awesome people, great atmosphere, and amazing food!
Everything I've ordered has been fantastic! Great service to accompany the amazing food.
Nice place to hang out and enjoy the veiw!
Food is alway amazing. Service is always above and beyond. Love everyone and everything about Graze. Great job!

Food and service are excellent. I haven’t tried a single thing I don’t like from their menu. If you want to have the best burger in town, you have to order the 1910 Burger. They have a prime spot in Armature Works with the best view of the river and downtown.
Large portions on their toasts and salads. Probably could have split our choices and still be full. Everything was excellent and the wait staff was helpful with all the choices.
Delicious and fast. Wonderful healthy alternative.

Is it the best burger and chicken in the world ? No. Is it acceptable and fairly priced , yes. Chicken sandwich was chewy, burger was  Meh. Just missing a true flavor or wow factor . Better options around .

I crave Graze 1910 on a weekly basis since my first visit.  "Build your own bowl" for breakfast with eggs, potatoes, poblanos, beans, and roasted tomatoes.  And 1910 burgers for the rest of the day.  Literally all day I could eat these burgers- lunch, dinner, dessert, snacks between meals, before meals, on the side with meals...  Do yourself a favor and try the 1910 and Graze burger just the way they come.  Don't try building a new recipe, don't ask for sauce on the side, just enjoy the original burger the way it was meant to be.  The location and atmosphere are badass.  Sit by the open bay windows when the weather is nice and enjoy the view of downtown Tampa, plus people watching is great.  The counter and stools at the bar are elegant; you will receive full service and dinnerware if you can find a spot.  Beverage selection is on point from breakfast through dinner- wide juice selection, great coffee, tea, beer, mimosas, wine.
I don't normally write reviews BUT I dream about the Chicken Salad Tartine from Graze 1910...it's crazy good!  Graze is my new fav spot to use for catering as well.  Love it.

Went to Tampa to visit friends and family for the weekend and was told to visit Graze. My friends have done it once again and recommended a fantastic place. Absolutely loved and enjoyed the food, the atmosphere and the staff were all super sweet. If you’re visiting from out of town definitely stop by Graze. You’ll LOVE it.

When in the mood for a terrific Hamburger friends and I will do a road trip 55 miles one way just to have the best Short Rib and Brisket Burgers around!  The staff is outstanding, all the menu items are delicious and the place is always clean.  The owners, Raymond & Lauren are proud of their brand and work very hard to provide the best service to the happy families and customer/friends that have made Graze 1910 their destination of choice for great food. Try the 1910 Burger...my favorite!

Great food.  I love to create my own bowls.  They cater to vegans, which was really important to me as I’m a nursing mother to a babe with dairy intolerance.  They go above and beyond to accommodate.  Staff was super friendly.  The atmosphere at armature is so inviting and Graze is definitely our spot 👌🏻 Beautiful views to the outside patio to watch our kids play too!!
Absolutely LOVE Graze 1910!! Who doesn’t love breakfast anytime? The staff is great and timely. Love the atmosphere! A must try - I promise you’ll get hooked!

From bowls to burgers EVERYTHING is so good! Staff is always friendly and love that you can sit up at the bar with full service :) Best place to eat at Armature! Do yourself a favor and also grab a Prosecco + Pop !
LOVE Graze 1910! Everything on the menu is delicious. Especially love the salmon tartine for breakfast. Super friendly staff! Great view too.

Burger: 5 stars Price for burger: -1 star  This little gem is one of many that is located inside of Armature Works. It is right next to the patio seating with games so you are able to enjoy this sitting inside, out on the bar seating or at one of the patio tables. The patio tables were very wobbly so I wouldn't recommend one until you've tested the table before sitting.  I got the Ray Ray BLT burger and I must say this burger was absolutely delicious. Would I get it again? Yes! For $9 with no sides? I don't know. The burger itself was delicious but for $9 and no sides, it kind of disappoints. There were other food vendors that offer a sandwich, drink and fries for $10 at lunch so for $9, I don't believe that I would get it again BUT it was delicious so there's sort of a mix there.  Awesome view, awesome staff and awesome food. Just missed me with the $9 price and no sides but other than that, it is a really cool joint!
Wonderful food and drinks!
Food is mediocre and really horrible service from Amanda. She was very disrespectful, Not family friendly. Would not recommend going.
I just wish they didnt play with my emotions & give us more tots.
Chicken and Waffles was delish! Great service, great food, fun atmosphere. I'll definitely be back!

I love how the chicken and waffles are available even at night. The waffles had good flavor. Chicken could've been just a tad crispier. I had it with maple bacon syrup. I didn't think anything of it when they didn't serve a side of syrup (it was just drizzled), but saw that one of my friends had syrup on the side. Maybe I need to ask next time. I loved the tator tots, it's packed in really tight so that when you bite into it, you get a full bite of potato and not just...pieces of shredded potatoes.
Loved Graze! Every time I go I get great service and food!! I recommend the avocado salad
Great food!  Great staff!  Definitely best place in Armature Works!
I love breakfast all day! Graze has so many good options!

Graze is our favorite place to eat at Armature. Their entire menu is simply delicious. A true crowd pleaser too - from burger lovers to brunch babes, vegan selection is super tasty, flavored milk shakes and ice pops for the kids, beer and champs for Mommy and Daddy (because, kids) and salads for that power lunch (side of tots because, life). Everything we've had was 5-star review worthy. We've been fans since day one and keep going back for more.  Side note: the owners are local and really good people. You can tell Graze is their baby in the quality of the food and the smiles in the service. We love this place.
Great people, food, and atmosphere! I go back every time I’m there!

Got our food.  The food was bad and dry.  Went up to the counter and asked for extra dressing.   Amanda “the manager”  rolled her eyes and was very rude. I asked her why the attitude,   she said go write a review my name is Amanda , or just deal with it. She said no matter what people will still come here.  I’m a big foodie, the food was 2 star at most.  Service was Terrible.  *Super rude and not family friendly as I was holding my 2 year old niece *
The food is amazing! Well prepared and didn't have to wait long to receive my food.
One of the best burger I have ever tried. Amazing
Delicious burger, a few more tots would be nice, but cooked to perfection!
